      "content": "The scientific consensus is clear that reducing vehicle miles traveled is essential for meeting climate targets, making the environmental necessity an objective reality. Congestion pricing is not a *preferred* policy; it is one of the most economically efficient and proven mechanisms to achieve that necessary reduction. While some ideologues prefer subsidies, the data overwhelmingly supports pricing externalities like traffic and pollution to force behavioral change.",
